## Building a Password Generator in Angular

**Mental model:** Build a character pool from the enabled option sets, then draw `length` random characters. Component fields hold the options; `generate()` runs on any change and on init. A getter derives the strength label. Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them), no `FormsModule` — use plain bindings + events.

### Step 1 — Fields
```typescript
length = 16;
opts: Record<string, boolean> = { lower: true, upper: true, digits: true, symbols: false };
password = '';
```

### Step 2 — Build the pool, draw characters
```typescript
generate(): void {
  const pool = this.keys.filter((k) => this.opts[k]).map((k) => this.SETS[k]).join('');
  if (!pool) { this.password = ''; return; }
  let out = '';
  for (let i = 0; i < this.length; i++) { out += pool[Math.floor(Math.random() * pool.length)]; }
  this.password = out;
}
```

### Step 3 — Regenerate on change
Call `generate()` from the range `(input)` and each checkbox `(change)`, and once in `ngOnInit`.

```html
<input type="range" [value]="length" (input)="length = +$any($event.target).value; generate()" />
```

### Step 4 — Strength getter
```typescript
get score(): number {
  const variety = this.keys.filter((k) => this.opts[k]).length;
  return Math.min(5, variety - 1 + (this.length >= 16 ? 2 : this.length >= 12 ? 1 : 0));
}
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| No sets enabled | Empty pool → empty password + a hint. |
| Strict types | `opts` typed as `Record<string, boolean>` for `[k]` access. |
| Crypto-strength | Use `crypto.getRandomValues` for real secrets. |

**Interview tip:** Without `FormsModule`, wiring the range/checkboxes through `(input)`/`(change)` + explicit `generate()` calls shows you can do reactive UI with just bindings — and note `crypto.getRandomValues` for production password strength.

